    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 126.</p><p>Cloak of Barbatos</p><p>10th-level necromancy</p><p>Classes: Cleric, Sorcerer, Warlock Casting Time: 1 action Range: self (15-foot radius, 5-foot-high cylinder) Components: V, S, M (a cigar of infernal tobacco worth at least 100 GP, which the spell consumes) Duration: Concentration, up to 1 minute</p><p>You exhale deathly smoke from your nose and mouth, which coalesces into a huge cloak of decay that wraps around you, killing everything in your path. The cloak is a 15-foot-radius, 5-foot-high cylinder that moves with you. Creatures that enter that area for the first time in a round of combat must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 8d6 x 10 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. A creature that is reduced to 0 hit points by this spell is liquified, dying instantly and having its body destroyed.</p></div>",
